England are through to the World Cup semi-finals for the first time since 1990. It bears repeating. England are through to the World Cup semi-finals for the first time since 1990. Blimey. A workman-like Sweden came to nulify an increasingly exciting England with an old-fashioned combination of 4-4-2 and long balls from the back. It didn't work. A 2-0 quarter-final victory over the Swedes had some tricky, tense moments. But, by the end, England had a new bunch of heroes and a set of fresh Ikea jokes. Let's re-live the historic match via the best moments on Twitter.    